Granite
-------
Granite is a development library for elementary development.

Granite is an extension to GTK. Among other things, it provides the
commonly-used widgets such as modeswitchers, welcome screens, AppMenus,
search bars, and more found in elementary apps.

Documentation
-------------
You can find the valadoc for Granite (documentation on all classes and
functions) at:

  http://valadoc.elementaryos.org/Granite/index.htm

Bugs
----
If you find bugs while installing or in Granite itself,
please report them at:

  https://launchpad.net/granite/+filebug

